quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  12,30,"And some women in the city said, \"The wife of the King´s Minister seeks to seduce her slave for his person; truly, he has infatuated (smitten) her with lust: verily, we see her in manifest error"
  12,31,"And when she heard of their malicious talk, she sent for them, and prepared for them a banquet, and gave each of them a knife; and she said (to Joseph), \"Come forth to them!\" And when they saw him they exalted (admired) him and cut their hands e"
  12,32,"Said she, \"There before you is he about whom you blamed me. I did seek to seduce him for his person, but he did save himself firmly, guiltless. But now if he does not what I bid him he shall surely be cast into prison and shall surely be among those"
  12,33,"Said he, \"O My Lord! Prison is dearer to me than what they call on me to do; and unless you turn from me their wiles I shall incline unto them and shall be among the foolish"
  12,34,"And his Lord answered him and turned from him their wiles; verily, He is Hearer, Knower"
  12,35,"Then it appeared good to them, even after they had seen the signs (of his innocence), to imprison him for a time"
  12,36,"And two young men went to prison with him. Said one of them, \"Verily, I dreamt that I was pressing wine.\" And the other said, \"Verily, I dreamt that I was bearing on my head loaves from which the birds did eat.\" \"Tell us\" (th)"
  12,37,"He said, \"I shall tell you both of its interpretation before your daily meal is brought to you. That is (some) of what my Lord has taught me; verily, I have forsaken the faith of a people who believe not in Allah, and disbelieve in the Hereafter"
  12,38,"And I have followed the faith of my fathers, Abraham and Isaac and Jacob. It never was for us to associate aught as partners with Allah. This is of the Bounty (or Grace) from Allah upon us and upon mankind: but most men give not thanks"
  12,39,"O you two fellow-prisoners! Are manifold lords better, or Allah, the One, the Almighty"
  12,40,"What you worship beside Him are naught but names which you have named, you and your fathers, for which Allah has sent down no authority. Judgment rests with Allah only, who commands you to worship none but Him. That is the right religion, but most men kno"
  12,41,"O you two fellow-prisoners! As for one of you, he shall pour out wine for his lord to drink: and as for the other, he shall be crucified, and the birds shall eat from his head. Thus is the matter decreed whereof you did inquire"
  12,42,"And he said to him of the two whom he knew would escape, \"Remember me with your Lord!\" But Satan made him forget to mention him to his lord, so he (Joseph) lingered in prison for a few more years"
  12,43,"And the king said, \"Verily, I saw in a dream seven fat kine which seven lean kine devoured; and seven green ears of corn and (seven) others dry. O you chiefs! Explain to me my vision, if dreams you can interpret"
  12,44,"Said they, \"Confused dreams! And naught know we of the interpretation of such dreams"
  12,45,"Then he of the twain who had escaped, remembered after a while, and said, \"Verily, I will inform you of the interpretation thereof, so send me forth"
  12,46,"(When he came to Joseph, he said) \"Joseph! O you truthful one! Explain to us the seven fat kine which seven lean ones devoured; and the seven green ears of corn and others dry that I may return to the people, per chance (or possibly) they then may kn"
  12,47,"He said, \"You shall sow for seven years, as is your wont; but what you reap, leave it in the ear, except a little whereof you eat"
  12,48,"Then there shall come after that seven severe years which shall devour what you have put by before for them, save a little which you shall preserve"
  12,49,Then there will come after that a year in which the people shall have abundant rain and in which they shall press (wine and oil)
  12,50,"Then the king (after he had been told) said, \"Bring him (Joseph) unto me.\" And when the messenger came unto him, Joseph said, \"Return to your Lord, and ask him, what is the state of mind of the women who cut their hands? Verily, my lord kno"
  12,51,"He (the king sent for the women and) said, \"What happened when you sought to seduce Joseph?\" They said, \"Allah preserve us! We know no evil of him.\" Said the wife of the Minister, \"Now is the truth exposed! It was I who sought to"
  12,52,"(The wife said) \"This, I asked that he (my lord) might know that I did not betray him in his absence, and that Allah guides not the guile of the betrayers"